President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has delegated authority to the Secretary of Defense to waive certain limitations on the cost of construction and repair projects in support of the Counter-ISIS campaign in Iraq and Syria. This delegation of authority is in accordance with sections 1209(l)(3) and 1236(o) of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2015, as amended. The Secretary of Defense is also authorized to make any determinations and submit any congressional notifications required for such waivers. This memorandum has been directed to be published in the Federal Register.